The longer connected passages have beon referred to their most probable sources The credit is divided between the two great Fathers of the Church, Augustino and Gregory the Great. In most instances we note that the ideas first uttered by the former were afterwards given hythe latter the form and scope in which they became generally current. This is true of the two important passages that I shall discuss next.
